al reality under Vijayanagara rule.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aHistory (General). 0aHistory of Asia. 0aIslam. Bahai Faith. Theosophy, etc. 0aReligion (General). 7aHISTORY / Asia / India & South Asia.2bisacsh  a16th century.  aacademic.  aally.  aancient city.  acity of victory.  aempire.  agovernment.  ahindu.  ahistorical.  aindia.  aindian government.  aindian history.  aindian politics.  akrishna river.  amilitary.  apolemics.  apolitical.  areligion.  arival.  arulers.  ascholarly.  asectarian.  asocial life.  asouth india.  atranslation.  aurban.  avijayanagara empire.  aworld history.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAsian Studies Contemporary Collection eBook Packagez978311064982608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2016z978311066754740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780520965461?locatt=mode:legacyzOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520965461zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520965461/original  a978-3-11-064982-6 Asian Studies Contemporary Collection eBook Package  a978-3-11-066754-7 University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA